description.plain:
Turran Coleman, best-known as his stage name, Luh Kel, is an American rapper, singer, and songwriter. Born in May 20, 2002. Coleman has dropped his viral single song “Wrong” with 19 million plays on Soundcloud.

Turran released his first studio album Mixed Emotions in November 2019 .

songs.title: Wrong

description.plain:
After gaining popular acclaim on Instagram under his moniker LifeWLuhKel, Luh Kel released his much-awaited debut single, “Wrong,” alongside a cinematic music video. The song boasts a heartbroken Luh Kel whose adoration for a girl has left after discovering she cheated on Kel with his friends.

The song immediately gained traction on video sharing sites, like dubsmash and TikTok, under the #WrongChallenge hashtag.

songs.title: Pull Up

description.plain: This snippet first made a debut on December 31st, 2018. Luh Kel made his first post on Instagram featuring the beat to Ne-Yo’s So Sick. The post was a 33-second video of him singing a few lines from his upcoming project. Two months later, on February 3rd, 2019 Luh Kel made a post featuring a 50-second video of him in his studio dancing along to the same verses, plus some more. However, the beat has been changed since.
